2360	  \begin{itemize}
2361	    \item[(C.a)] \emph{FREE-CASE.} Over $k$ of characteristic $0$, if the universal K\"ahler derivation $D$ kills $f \in \mathrm{MvPolynomial}\,\sigma\,k$ (i.e.\ $D f = 0$), then $f \in (\mathrm{MvPolynomial.C}).\mathrm{range}$ ($f$ is a constant). Proof: $D f = 0$ forces every partial $\mathrm{pderiv}_i f = 0$ (via the explicit free basis \texttt{KaehlerDifferential.mvPolynomialBasis}, with $\mathrm{repr}(D f)\,i = \mathrm{pderiv}_i f$); the coefficient identity $\mathrm{coeff}_{u - \mathrm{single}_i 1}(\mathrm{pderiv}_i f) = \mathrm{coeff}_u f \cdot (u\,i)$ for $u\,i \geq 1$ then forces every non-constant coefficient to vanish in characteristic $0$ (where the integer $u\,i$ is invertible). \textbf{Closed in Lean}: project lemmas \texttt{\_mvPoly\_coeff\_pderiv\_at\_shifted}, \texttt{\_mvPoly\_mem\_range\_C\_of\_pderiv\_eq\_zero}, \texttt{\_mvPoly\_mem\_range\_C\_of\_D\_eq\_zero} (\texttt{AlgebraicJacobian/Cotangent/ChartAlgebra.lean}; \texttt{private}, not in Mathlib).
2362	    \item[(C.b)] \emph{Standard-smooth presentation.} Extract a \texttt{SubmersivePresentation}\,$P$ from the \texttt{Algebra.IsStandardSmoothOfRelativeDimension}\,$n$\,$k$\,$B$ hypothesis (via \texttt{Algebra.IsStandardSmooth.out}), giving a polynomial ring $P.\mathrm{Ring} = \mathrm{MvPolynomial}\,\iota\,k$ together with a surjective $k$-algebra map $\pi = \mathtt{algebraMap}\,P.\mathrm{Ring}\,B$ (surjectivity by \texttt{Algebra.Generators.algebraMap\_surjective}). \textbf{Closed in Lean.}
2363	    \item[(C.c)] \emph{Lift $+$ functoriality.} Lift $b \in B$ to $\tilde b \in P.\mathrm{Ring}$ along the surjection $\pi$; the functoriality identity \texttt{KaehlerDifferential.map\_D} turns the hypothesis $D_B b = 0$ into $(\mathtt{map}\,k\,k\,P.\mathrm{Ring}\,B)(D_A \tilde b) = 0$, i.e.\ $D_A \tilde b \in \ker(\mathtt{map}\,k\,k\,P.\mathrm{Ring}\,B)$. \textbf{Closed in Lean} (the \texttt{\_hFunct} step).
2364	    \item[(C.d)] \emph{Transfer step --- the residual \texttt{sorry}.} Modify $\tilde b$ to some $\alpha \in P.\mathrm{Ring}$ with $\pi(\alpha) = b$ (same image under the presentation map) AND $D_A \alpha = 0$ in $\Omega_{P.\mathrm{Ring}/k}$; then (C.a) applied to $\alpha$ gives $\alpha \in (\mathrm{MvPolynomial.C}).\mathrm{range}$, and the scalar-tower factorisation $\mathtt{algebraMap}\,k\,B = \pi \circ (\mathrm{MvPolynomial.C})$ yields $b \in \operatorname{range}(\mathtt{algebraMap}\,k\,B)$. The obstruction to producing $\alpha$ is the description of the kernel: by \texttt{KaehlerDifferential.ker\_map\_of\_surjective}, $\ker(\mathtt{map}\,k\,k\,P.\mathrm{Ring}\,B)$ is the $P.\mathrm{Ring}$-submodule generated by $\{D r : r \in I\}$ (where $I = \ker \pi$) together with the $I \cdot \Omega_{P.\mathrm{Ring}/k}$ part. Subtracting a Leibniz combination $\sum_j a_j r_j$ ($r_j \in I$) absorbs the $D(I)$ part, leaving $D_A \alpha_1 \in I \cdot \Omega_{P.\mathrm{Ring}/k}$, and freeness of $\Omega_{P.\mathrm{Ring}/k}$ on $\{\mathrm dx_i\}$ reads this as ``each $\mathrm{pderiv}_i \alpha_1 \in I$''. Two closure paths: \textbf{(S5.a)} explicit \texttt{ker\_map\_of\_surjective} unfolding $+$ \texttt{Finsupp.linearCombination} unpacking $+$ Leibniz iteration ($\sim 30$ LOC); \textbf{(S5.b)} abstract bypass via \texttt{Algebra.FormallySmooth.subsingleton\_h1Cotangent} (the $H^1$ cotangent-complex vanishing for formally smooth $B$) deriving $\ker D_B \subseteq \operatorname{range}(\mathtt{algebraMap}\,k\,B)$ directly ($\sim 10$--$20$ LOC). \textbf{This is the single residual \texttt{sorry}} in the KDM Lean body; it is the iter-151+ prover target.
2365	  \end{itemize}
